  "parent": "x-clade-sout3147",
  "notes": "Standard Croatian (Štokavian Ijekavian dialect basis). Latin script only (unlike Serbian). Shares the two palatal affricate pairs with Serbian: ⟨ć⟩ = [tɕ] (softer), ⟨č⟩ = [tʃ] (harder); ⟨đ⟩ = [dʑ], ⟨dž⟩ = [dʒ]. Four-pitch-accent system. Syllabic /r̩/ (e.g. *prst* 'finger'). Ijekavian: Proto-Slavic yat /æː/ → ije/je (vs Serbian Ekavian e).",
